A vintage 1960s-style technical illustration showing a complex filing cabinet with one drawer pulled open, revealing interconnected XML data streams flowing out like ribbons of punch cards. Inside the drawer, small glowing orbs represent buddy contacts, organized in neat rows but connected by thin golden threads forming a network pattern. The scene is rendered in muted olive greens, warm browns, and cream colors with subtle halftone dot textures typical of mid-century technical manuals. A magnifying glass hovers over the open drawer, its lens revealing the hidden binary structure beneath the surface data.
